dPress optimization plugin. In an upcoming release, users will soon be able to use an all-new Minify feature that will &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize-to-release-new-minify-feature/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize-to-release-new-minify-feature/\">WP-Optimize to release new Minify feature</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Wayne Mullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1974:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We are happy to share with you that <a href=\"https://getwpo.com/\">WP-Optimize</a> will soon be adding an exciting new feature to our popular WordPress optimization plugin. In an upcoming release, users will soon be able to use an all-new Minify feature that will help make their websites run even faster.</span></p>\n<p><b>How does minification work?</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The minify process works by removing all the unnecessary characters from a piece of code, such as line breaks, white spaces etc. The minified code still works exactly the same as it did before the minification process, but the files now take up less space due to the removal of unnecessary information. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This process has proved to have been very popular when being used on scripts, stylesheets and and other components on your website which can benefit from faster loading times. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Minify feature will further reduce HTTP requests to help speed up your site. This works by merging CSS and Javascript files into a group of files and attempting to use as few of these files as possible.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our new Minify feature will be simple to use and intuitive. Most users just need to set it to default settings and let it do it’s thing. This new feature will be launched soon, so be sure to keep an eye out for it in an upcoming release of </span><a href=\"https://getwpo.com/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WP-Optimize</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize-to-release-new-minify-feature/\">WP-Optimize to release new Minify feature</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-optimize-to-release-new-minify-feature/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:4:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"How to integrate Slack reminder notification with WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/UpdraftPlus/~3/Dr_dSp_IZP8/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 07 Feb 2020 11:49:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Tips and tricks\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"slack message reminder serup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"slack notification setup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"slack reminder\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://updraftplus.com/?p=509161\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:760:\"<p>With so many different demands vying for your attention in modern life, it can be easy to lose track of the many important tasks you are supposed to carry out and hopefully be reminded of. After all, there is only &#8230; <a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-integrate-slack-reminder-notification-with-wordpress/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-integrate-slack-reminder-notification-with-wordpress/\">How to integrate Slack reminder notification with WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Wayne Mullins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19201:\"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With so many different demands vying for your attention in modern life, it can be easy to lose track of the many important tasks you are supposed to carry out and hopefully be reminded of. After all, there is only so much a desk full of scribbled post-it notes can do to ensure you are reminded about something important, so there is a good chance you have forgotten about something recently. However, there is a way to get Slack to remind you of all these tasks as and when you require, and the good news is we are going to show you how to set it up!   </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There can be a large number of things you may need Slack to remind you of. The who, what, when and why of a reminder is hugely important and can cover anything from setting a reminder of a meeting with your bank manager, submitting your travelling expenses on time or a reminder for a deadline of an important project coming up. The reminder example we will be using in this blog is setting up a “blog post Slack reminder&#8221; message. Though feel free to substitute this for any kind of reminder that is more appropriate to you and your situation.     </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Given the importance of SEO, most people who run websites are aware of vital regularly updating and posting new blogs is. While the tasks needed to succeed at SEO are a closely guarded secret, we do know that regularly posting a new blog is a great way to move up the Google SEO ranking. As such, website owners may be interested in an app for Slack that will send a notification to your Slack channel if you have not posted a new article on your blog within the last 7 days. These reminders will hopefully help you manage your articles and blogs better and also help to remind you to publish them on time.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In this article, we show you how you can integrate Slack notification with your WordPress blog using an app you can create yourself.</span></p>\n<p><b>Getting started &#8211; Create a Slack application</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To get started, you first need to create an application within your Slack account. To do this, go to the</span><a href=\"https://api.slack.com/apps\"> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Slack API</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> page and hit the &#8216;Create New App&#8217; button.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-509171 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"309\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru.png 1600w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-300x58.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-1024x198.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-768x148.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-1536x297.png 1536w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-1080x209.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/18H23PPbM_FaaaN8Cucx6GWk_FPOo_-9xMBUY2Ezt_oFLmognCbpOk9M4Hv9YQRh3EfirJuWlj6oMurowhkPov9eHe5aFb2UmwCJ6EF9VOSdM5eZJdHD-dVUAEmlR1NhMU7erwru-510x98.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This will create a popup window. Complete your details requested and you will be redirected to a ”settings page”. In this settings page, click on the &#8216;Incoming Webhooks&#8217; from the left section. Toggle this option to “On”.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-509179 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1380\" height=\"440\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT.png 1380w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT-300x96.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT-1024x326.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT-768x245.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT-1080x344.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/RbSYMfvMBlYSC47eeo0MM9UzlF6Q21MAlVCnc8P-dVmMvsvVguGQlD17tp-e4gcMsmr85G4VVtXWQT2DtsOU9MZC_C8R2YzVUwpjY3oeVZF5CGT_952ZWvULgCGmkf-NSqexYOqT-510x163.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1380px) 100vw, 1380px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scroll down to the bottom and click on the &#8216;Request to Add New Webhook&#8217; button. If you are not an Admin then you need to get admin approval to access this option.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-3.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-509181 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"686\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-3.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-3-300x112.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-3-510x190.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 686px) 100vw, 686px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once the app is approved, click on the &#8216;Install APP&#8217; from the left side menu. And then press the &#8216;Install App to Workspace&#8217; button.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-509182 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1438\" height=\"460\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9.png 1438w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9-300x96.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9-1024x328.png 1024w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9-768x246.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9-1080x345.png 1080w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/5AhEfNRSSTOmGSeV8tG-ZxROJpv_whGvvh8gFeLJXhdlou0RL6FUkJ-zVFIQd-Qpor3jzVyogAAa8LOf-bqERlPTyoWShjosKu0bOWaJWkNW8yLwwqk7_9J9S4EWhPI8pOxOiUM9-510x163.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1438px) 100vw, 1438px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Choose the desired channel on the next page and click on the &#8216;Allow&#8217; button. You will then be redirected to a page where you will get your Webhook URL. Copy this URL as you will require it shortly.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-4.png\"><img class=\"wp-image-509183 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"648\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-4.png 512w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-4-300x95.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/unnamed-4-510x161.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px\" /></a></p>\n<p><b>Send notification on Slack channel from WordPress</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You are now ready to proceed as you have the Webhook URL and have also configured the Slack channel, where the notification will be sent. Next, you need to write a code that sends a POST request along with a message to the webhook URL. This webhook URL will automatically post the received message to the chosen Slack channel. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So, let’s do some coding.</span></p>\n<p><b>Calculate days when last article is posted</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When sending a notification to the Slack channel, you first need to calculate days from when the last article was posted. The below code will go inside your active themes:</span><code>functions.php</code> file.</p>\n<pre style=\"background: #efefef;\"><code>&lt;?php\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">function get_daycount_of_last_blog_posted(){\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   $args=array(\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        \'post_type\' =&gt; \'post\',\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        \'post_status\' =&gt; \'publish\',\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        \'posts_per_page\' =&gt; 1,       \n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    );</span>  \n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    $datediff = 0;\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    $blog_posts = new WP_Query( $args );\n</span>    if ( $blog_posts-&gt;have_posts() ) :\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> \n while ( $blog_posts-&gt;have_posts() ) : $blog_posts-&gt;the_post();\n\n   $datediff = time() - strtotime(get_the_date());\n      endwhile;\n        wp_reset_postdata();\n    endif;</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    if ($datediff) return round($datediff / (60 * 60 * 24));</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">   return $datediff;\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This code and method will get the last added post from the WordPress database and calculate the days between when you requested it and when the last article was posted.</span></p>\n<p><b>Send POST request to Webhook</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">WordPress provides a function <i>wp_remote_post()</i> that performs an HTTP request and receives the response. Using this method we will send our custom message to the webhook.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create a file <code>notification.php</code> in the root directory of your WordPress project and add the below code to it.</span></p>\n<pre style=\"background: #efefef;\"><code><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&lt;?php \n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">require_once(\'wp-load.php\');\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">$slack_webhook_url = \'YOUR_WEBHOOK_URL\';\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">$last_blog_day_count = get_daycount_of_last_blog_posted();\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">if($last_blog_day_count &gt; 5) {</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> $msg = \'Hey team, our app found that we have not added new article on UpdraftPlus\n for more than 5 days. Please look into it.\';</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    // Prepare the data / payload to be posted to Slack\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  $data = array(\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        \'payload\'   =&gt; json_encode( array(\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">                \"text\" =&gt;  $msg,\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">            )\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        )\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    );</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    // Post our data via the slack webhook endpoint using wp_remote_post\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  wp_remote_post( $slack_webhook_url, array(\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">            \'method\' =&gt; \'POST\',\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">            \'body\' =&gt; $data,\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">        )\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">    );\n</span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This code will post a message to Webhook URL if a new article is not added for more than 5 days on your blog. As a result, you get a notification on your selected Slack channel.</span></p>\n<p><b>Set cron on your server</b></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Our goal is to create an automated system which will notify the team about this task on a specific Slack channel. Because of this, we created a PHP file in the root folder of the WordPress project. By setting cron with this file on your server, you can set up your Slack app to run automatically.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Setting cron on the server may differ on the basis of your hosting provider. For the sake of this tutorial, we will give an example on how to set cron on Media Temple web hosting&#8217;s CPanel.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Login to your CPanel. Select &#8216;Cron Jobs&#8217; under the “Advanced” section.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-509184 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"994\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh.png 994w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh-300x99.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh-768x253.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/XJRZ1skju2esDJFf4JDq5q7eZkJxTC9yf-myua5-H_nMHEp8T_OWMk3zKjRaedfbkNKR_n_KErfgoY89QpTsQzHjtKDK7Us4G_Xf2J1nzhWz3szGkvuSyrk7Mqgqiitx_tKI_AJh-510x168.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 994px) 100vw, 994px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On the next page, choose the &#8216;Once Per Day(0 0 * * *)&#8217; option from the &#8216;Common Settings&#8217; dropdown. This means the cron will execute the script once a day.</span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-509185 aligncenter\" src=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"896\" height=\"706\" srcset=\"https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU.png 896w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU-300x236.png 300w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU-768x605.png 768w, https://updraftplus.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/CMmgq4GVjx6wWdFMDJydgQBj2zxyL4qufL3YBbTqAX5_zyEsTPPa6GZGxOCi1-0X-uhIHk12GckxlsnNevqvJhx-UzgKh_YP6YEJUoVbIPMtT0UijQa1da05BSi8A60JdV3R00WU-510x402.png 510w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 896px) 100vw, 896px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Finally, in the Command field add the below statement by adjusting your <code>notification.php</code> file path.</span></p>\n<pre style=\"background: #efefef;\"><code><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&lt;pre&gt;/usr/local/bin/php /home/xyz/public_html/notification.php&lt;/pre&gt;</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">That&#8217;s it! </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By following this tutorial, you are now able to create your own Slack app for you and your team. This will certainly help everyone keep up to date with scheduled blogs and ensure you do not miss out on any important dates. </span></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com/how-to-integrate-slack-reminder-notification-with-wordpress/\">How to integrate Slack reminder notification with WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus</a>. <a href=\"http://updraftplus.com\">UpdraftPlus - Backup, restore and migration plugin for WordPress.</a></p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rss